            <abstract id="ref2" label="Abstract">There are several letters which concern Lukens' official position as Surveyor-general, but the bulk of the collection is the 12 small survey books (1760-1775, ca. 108 p.). There are surveys of Philadelphia, particularly near the State House, now Independence Square; for a vineyard plantation in the Northern Liberties (1769); and for lands in Lancaster and Berks Counties.</abstract>
            <physdesc id="ref1" label="General Physical Description note">
                <extent>12 volumes, 106 p.; 4 items.</extent></physdesc>
